snippet.textDisplay: In my opinion and as far as the 2 episodes have gone of this season.. this season has not been appealing and inspiring to me. I have followed all seasons where there was a time when a person had the urge of what's coming next and every track used to be a master piece. Putting in BiG artists doesn't mean that the song will become super hit. It's the music director / producer job to create something new, something a person after listening repeats on their tounge and listen to it again and again. But so far only one song from episode of this season by Momina and Danyal was better as compared. Even junoon killed their own song in this episode by Salman Ahmed. There are no funky, upbeat tracks which makes your mood. Even the sad songs are not even upto the mark. Don't understand if the Strings (with all due respect) are still experimenting or what they r trying to do. Rohail Hayyat was way way better than everyone in all the episodes of Coke Studio, whether anyone likes it or Not. I think Coke Studio Pakistan should start thinking from now for next year else it's a downfall for a super hit program which is followed by worldwide audience.
